    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-08-07T09:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-08-07T09:00:00-05:00" n="855"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d855">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">684A.85/8–754: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 855<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Egypt (<persName corresp="#p_CJ1"
                            type="from">Caffery</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d855fn1">Repeated to London, Amman, Jerusalem, and Tel
                        Aviv.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Cairo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-08-07T16:00:00+02:00"
                            >August 7, 1954—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>179. Reference: <gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 205.<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d855fn2">Printed as telegram 38 to Amman, <ref target="#d853"
                            >Document 853</ref>.</note> Embassy found opportunity sound out
                        <persName corresp="#p_GLCS1">Gohar</persName> re current Egyptian position
                    on local commanders agreements today.</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_GLCS1">Gohar</persName> said he has repeatedly told
                    Israelis situation Gaza Strip unlike Jordan since only fifty kilometers long and
                    they can come to Egyptian checkpost any time and he or other officer can meet
                    them within 15 minutes. <persName corresp="#p_GLCS1">Gohar</persName> has also
                    repeatedly urged police sub-committee be set up to handle minor questions.</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_GLCS1">Gohar</persName> said Israelis always refuse any
                    arrangement involving police officers and <gloss target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss>
                    observers and insist that “local commanders” should meet.</p>
                <p>Re Israeli attitude, <persName corresp="#p_GLCS1">Gohar</persName> said it is on
                    record in minutes of <gloss target="#t_EIMAC1">EIMAC</gloss> that Israelis said
                    “It is better to kill the infiltrator than to hand him over”.</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">Comment:</hi>
                    <persName corresp="#p_DBGM1">Dayan</persName> emphasis on direct contact between
                    “officers” believed here to indicate Israeli desire exclude <gloss
                        target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss> observers and avoid practical arrangements at
                    police level.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_CJ1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Caffery</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
